          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      This follows Leeâ€™s recent election victory, suggesting a potential shift in Seoulâ€™s foreign policy. South Korean foreign policy tends to lean more towards the US and Japan, a trend that was evident under former president Yoon Suk Yeol. The deterioration in US ties stemmed from the deployment of a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-jun-25-spotlight-h1-2-us-missile-defense-system?source=website" target="_blank">US missile defense system</a> in South Korea in 2017.</p>
